        [
          "Staff Generated History"
        ],
        [
          "Sometimes you remember your life in the asylum.  As a doctor you counseled the patients you could help and dissected those you couldn't.  It was during one fo these dissections that your subject tore out your throat and left you to bleed on the stone floor of the asylum's operating theatre.  He ran off screaming into the night, looping his intestines back into his open abdomen.  As you died you found her, the Lady of the Maze.  She led you through the labyrinth and back into the dead flesh of your cold body.  Your mind's incurable madness and your body's death turned you from trusted colleague to coveted oddity.  While your former peers poked your psyche and prodded your flesh, you delved into the contours of your own mind. There you herd the whispers of the Lady of the Maze and found the writing of the Fey written upon its strange gray walls, you leanred of the dark mother Lilith and how she sheltered and mentored Caine in the Land of Nod.  You don't know how they found you, but the Sabbat rescued from the Asylum in 1906. Your pack was astounded by your insight and knowledge of the vampiric mysteries and were further astounded that you'd managed to shed your Humanity without a teacher.  They annointed you their priest and as they helped you delve into your mind in search of the Lady of the Maze, they renamed the pack in your honor and one by one fell to tragedy and madness. Although Alabastor knows some of the story and suspects you hold great power within you, you are the only surviving member of the original pack.  Today you continue your own explorations of the maze within your mind, but keep your secrets to yourself in hopes of safeguarding your packmates from a darker fate."
        ],
        [
          "Sire:",
          "Unknown",
          "Reference: (If any)",
